<emphasis bold="true" box="[1245,1266,1961,1987]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">D</emphasis>
. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="122.[189,1399,266,397]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">LEGS. Pro- and mesoleg yellow, tarsomeres 4 and 5 black. Metaleg with coxa black, trochanter yellow, femur black and yellow biannulate, slightly incrassate, ratio width: length 1: 3.9–4.3; tibia black and yellow biannulate with wide, short, rounded apicoventral dens; tarsus entirely black, basitarsomere rather thin, ratio width: length 1: 3.6–4.0.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="122.[189,1399,437,674]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
ABDOMEN. Length ratio of terga I: II: III: IV 1: 4.2–4.4: 2.0–2.1: 1.8–1.9; ratio width at posterior margin: medial length of tergum II and III 1: 4.4–4.7 and 1: 1.0–1.1. Terga black, tergum II anteriorly with mediolateral small light-brown macula; anterior 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[703,725,507,533]" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">⅓</emphasis>
of tergum III with yellow fascia with posterior margin deeply incised; pile pale, on terga short, laterally on terga I and II long; tergum I with a row of 2–3 strong light-brown setae at lateral margin; sternum III rectangular, ratio width: length 1: 1.6–1.9; sterna VI, VII and VIII (
<figureCitation box="[304,411,613,639]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="121.[189,232,1925,1951]" captionTargetBox="[194,1394,818,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@121.[189,1399,815,1894]" captionTargetPageId="121" captionText="Fig. 58. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) lucida sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Sterna IV, VI and VII, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe with associated parts, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830670/files/figure.png" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Fig. 58A</figureCitation>
) with long yellow pile, sternum VIII with low widely rounded elevation posteriorly. Genitalia, 
<figureCitation box="[311,395,648,674]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="121.[189,232,1925,1951]" captionTargetBox="[194,1394,818,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@121.[189,1399,815,1894]" captionTargetPageId="121" captionText="Fig. 58. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) lucida sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Sterna IV, VI and VII, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe with associated parts, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830670/files/figure.png" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
B–D: note the asymmetrical surstyli and superior lobes.
</paragraph>
